History of Present Illness (HPI):
The patient has been trying to go to bed earlier but struggles with late-night activities, primarily scrolling through their phone or watching shows. 
       - They feel sluggish and find it hard to focus at work, often zoning out during tasks that require concentration. 
       - The patient has been going out more socially, which can be draining, and they need alone time afterward to recharge.
Therapeutic Interventions:
The patient is open to exploring mindfulness techniques to help improve focus and manage feelings of being overwhelmed. 
       - A simple breathing exercise was introduced, which the patient found helpful and is willing to incorporate into their routine.
Next Steps:
The patient plans to track their phone usage and practice mindfulness during breaks at work. 
       - They also intend to schedule alone time after social events to prioritize self-care.
